<p>Hatter is an HTML templating language that can be used server side to produce static HTML. Its syntax is a cheap knock-off of <a href="https://imba.io">Imba</a>, without any of the fancy JavaScript parts.</p>
<p>It‚Äôs like a less powerful, 90s-era PHP. But we‚Äôre talking PHP/FI, none of that easy bake oven PHP3 stuff that you could use to build actual sites.</p>
<p>If you‚Äôre feeling adventerous, or mad as a hatter, you can use the standalone binary to turn templates into HTML files, or include the zero-dependency Rust library in your (web/cli/?) application.</p>
